pageContext.claim: “I think that instead of 3.2 [GDP growth in the first quarter of 2019], we could be in the fours and maybe even in the early fives. And I've always said that. But I have an artificial barrier, it's called The Fed. The Fed has been terrible, to me and despite that, I'm pulling through and you know, it's one of those things. But we would have been, we would have been 10,000 points up [in the Dow Jones] and we would have been in the 4s and maybe even better than that.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no basis for Trump's claim that GDP growth and stock market gains would soar without higher interest rates. The Federal Reserve has raised rates to prevent the economy from overheating and falling into recession.
